@mfenniak Your observation is correct. This PR fixes only a special case.

I had a similar thought yesterday while thinking about the problem but did not have any idea how to fix this -- but thinking about this again, we might be able to fix it, if we first `forward` and afterwards update (`put`) the state... 

\cc @dguy @bbejeck @enothereska @guozhangwang -- I am just wondering, if updating the state as last action for *all* processors would make sense in general?
